            <fr:route>/jms-00LX/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Finite set">Finite set</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be <html:em><html:strong>finite</html:strong></html:em> or have <html:em><html:strong>finite cardinality</html:strong></html:em> when it is <fr:link href="/jms-00L0/" title="Isomorphic sets" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L0/" display-uri="jms-00L0" type="local">isomorphic</fr:link> to a set of the form <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>; in this case, we therefore have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\#}{A}=n]]></fr:tex>. (Recall that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is the standard <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-element</html:span> set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{i\in \mathbb {N}\,\middle \vert \,0\leq  i < n\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.)</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>25</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LJ/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>jms-00LJ</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/jms-00LJ/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Properties of isomorphism">Properties of <fr:link href="/jms-00L0/" title="Isomorphic sets" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L0/" display-uri="jms-00L0" type="local">isomorphism</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>The concept of <fr:link href="/jms-00L0/" title="Isomorphic sets" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L0/" display-uri="jms-00L0" type="local">isomorphism</fr:link> between two sets satisfies laws like those of an <fr:link href="/jms-00L4/" title="Equivalence relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L4/" display-uri="jms-00L4" type="local">equivalence relation</fr:link>. In particular:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>reflexivity: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  A]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
 <html:li>transitivity: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  B \land  B \cong  C \implies  A \cong  C]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
 <html:li>symmetry: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  B \implies  B\cong  A]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="/marcelofiore/" title="Marcelo Fiore" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/marcelofiore/" display-uri="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>23</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L1/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>jms-00L1</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/jms-00L1/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Examples of isomorphic sets">Examples of <fr:link href="/jms-00L0/" title="Isomorphic sets" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L0/" display-uri="jms-00L0" type="local">isomorphic sets</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <fr:link href="/jms-00KR/" title="Bijection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KR/" display-uri="jms-00KR" type="local">bijection</fr:link> between finite sets is just a “relabeling” of its elements: for example, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{0,1\right \}\mathclose {}}\cong {\mathopen {}\left \{\mathsf {false},\mathsf {true}\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Isomorphism of infinite sets can be more confusing: for example, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\cong {\mathopen {}\left \{n:\mathbb {N}\,\middle \vert \,n>0\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\cong \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\cong \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\cong \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>, and even <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\to \mathbb {N}\right )\mathclose {}}\cong \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
